org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode

Class HardwareSPQR

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode.HardwareSPQR

  • public class HardwareSPQR
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines all hardware on the robot. It also contains common abstractions to interact with hardware.

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init(com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.HardwareMap m)
        This method initializes the hardware on the robot including sensors, servos, and motors. This method should be updated whenever a hardware device is added or removed, or when a device's settings need to be modified. This method should be called once.
        Parameters:
        m - The hardware map of the class instance of the callee to be assigned to the instance of hardware.

      • setDriveZeroPowerBehavior

        public void setDriveZeroPowerBehavior(com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.DcMotor.ZeroPowerBehavior behavior)
        This method sets the drive behavior of what one of the drive motors of the robot are to do when its power is set to zero.
        Parameters:
        behavior - A ZeroPowerBehavior enumeration (Under DcMotor) which will be applied to all of the drive motors of the robot.

      • setDriveMode

        public void setDriveMode(com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.DcMotor.RunMode mode)
        This method sets the drive mode of all of the drive motors.
        Parameters:
        mode - a RunMode enumeration (Under DcMotor) which will be applied to all of the drive motors of the robot.

        public void strafe(org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode.Dir direction,
                   double power)

        Parameters:
        direction - A Dir enumeration which states which direction the robot will strafe.
        power - A double between -1.0 and 1.0 which represents the speed at which the robot is to strafe.

      • tank

        public void tank(double left,
                 double right)
        This method takes two powers and sets the left motors to a given power and a right motors to a given power respectively.
        Parameters:
        left - A double between -1.0 and 1.0 which determines the speed that the left motors will be set to.
        right - A double between -1.0 and 1.0 which determines the speed that the right motors will be set to.

      • stopMoving

        public void stopMoving()
        This method stops the movement of the drive motors. If the motors are set to brake on zero power the robot will stop in place.

      • setDriveTargetPosition

        public void setDriveTargetPosition(int target)
        This method sets the same target position to all of the drive motors of the robot. The motors still need to be given power to move to the position.
        Parameters:
        target - An integer which is the target, in encoder units, for the robot to go to.

      • updateRobotPosition

        public void updateRobotPosition()
        This method updates the position of the robot according to the detected navigation targets. The updated location can be accessed through the location variable.
